Subject: Re: [T2] lifters et.al.

At 09:43 AM 10/24/2002, Faster-Laster wrote:
>There is also the question that if the lifters are always pressed
>against the cam (such as in a hyd setup) there is less lubrication
>between these. I keep hearing that a hyd cam is no good after 100k or
>so, due to the wear that takes place. 

I have seen a lot more wear on solid-lifter cams than hydraulic.  The hydraulic cams always seem to look like new.  The hydraulic cam in my engine has well over 100k miles on it and last time I looked at it (admittedly it was a few years ago) it showed no visible wear at all.

-David
